        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-11T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/8–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-11T12:00:00-04:00">August 11, 1945—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2510. Dept received last night through Swiss Legation here text of Japanese
                    surrender terms contained urtel 3864 August 10, 8 p.m. <pb facs="0645" n="633" xml:id="pg_633"/> Our reply on behalf of the four governments was delivered
                    to the Swiss Chargé d’Affaires at 10:30 a.m. today and text has been made
                    public.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
